# Agent tools & MCPs (Nativz Cortex)

## Workflow (non-negotiable for scoped asks)

When the user asks for something that maps to a **deployment platform, database, browser automation, library docs, payments, or design tools**, **use the matching MCP first** (after reading that tool’s JSON schema under `mcps/<server>/tools/`), then apply **project skills** (`.claude/skills/`, `.agents/skills/`, `CLAUDE.md` “Skills” references). Use **grep/read/run_terminal_cmd** only when no MCP fits or MCP is unavailable.

| User intent | MCP server (this workspace) | Skills to pair |
|-------------|-----------------------------|----------------|
| Vercel deploys, logs, projects, docs | `plugin-vercel-vercel` | Vercel skills from hooks / `vercel-*` in plugin cache |
| Supabase schema, SQL, project DB | `project-0-Nativz_Cortex-supabase` | `.agents/skills/supabase-postgres-best-practices/SKILL.md`, `docs/database.md` |
| Up-to-date library docs / examples | `plugin-compound-engineering-context7` | `framework-docs-researcher`, dependency-specific skills |
| Real browser driving (Playwright plugin) | `plugin-playwright-playwright` | `qa-loop`, e2e / Playwright patterns |
| Cursor IDE browser (lock/snapshot/profile) | `cursor-ide-browser` | Same as browser QA |
| Semantic code symbols / replace symbol | `plugin-serena-serena` | cortex-review, explore |
| Stripe (after auth) | `plugin-stripe-stripe` | stripe skills in plugin cache |
| Figma (after auth) | `plugin-figma-figma` | `figma-use`, `figma-implement-design` |

**Before any `call_mcp_tool`:** read the tool’s descriptor JSON (`description`, `parameters`, `required`) so arguments match the schema.

**Auth:** If the server exposes `mcp_auth`, call it so the user can authenticate before other tools appear.

