## Built-in Cursor / agent tools (categories)

These are not MCPs; use them for repo work and orchestration:

- **Search & navigate:** semantic codebase search, grep/ripgrep, glob file search  
- **Files:** read, write, apply patch / search-replace, delete, list directory  
- **Terminal:** run commands (tests, build, scripts)  
- **Tasks:** delegate parallel exploration or multi-step work to subagents when appropriate  
- **Web:** web search, fetch URL  
- **MCP:** `call_mcp_tool`, `list_mcp_resources`, `fetch_mcp_resource`  
- **Quality:** linter diagnostics, image generation (when asked), notebook edit  

